---
id: org.dxos.plugin.library
name: LibraryPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Library is a personal reading list built on ECHO. A book has a public, catalog-eligible face
(title, authors, reading status, rating, review, genres) and a private face that never leaves the
space (notes, ownership, personal tags). The public face maps to a `buzz.bookhive.book` atproto
record so the generic atproto companion can publish it to the user's PDS.

## Extensions

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |

## Types

```mdl
type Book
  desc: A book in the reading list. Public fields map to buzz.bookhive.book; private fields are ECHO-only.
  fields:
    title: string                                   # public
    authors: string[]                               # public
    status?: finished | reading | wantToRead | abandoned   # public
    stars?: number                                  # public, 1..10
    review?: string                                 # public
    startedAt?: string                              # public
    finishedAt?: string                             # public
    genres: string[]                                # public
    hiveId?: string                                 # public, BookHive catalog id
    hiveBookUri?: string                            # public
    coverUrl?: string                               # public
    notes?: string                                  # private
    owned?: boolean                                 # private
    format?: string                                 # private
    purchasePrice?: number                          # private
    purchaseDate?: string                           # private
    shelfLocation?: string                          # private
    personalTags: string[]                          # private
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Reading list CRUD in the content group
  req F-1.1: The Book type appears as a section in the navigation tree's content group.
  req F-1.2: A book can be created, renamed, opened as a full-page editable form, and deleted.
  req F-1.3: Collection tiles render a card body (cover, authors, status, rating).

feat F-2: BookHive-backed create autocomplete
  req F-2.1: The create form offers a type-ahead over the public buzz.bookhive.searchBooks endpoint.
  req F-2.2: Selecting a result autofills title, authors, coverUrl, genres, hiveId, hiveBookUri.

feat F-3: Publishable public face
  req F-3.1: The Book type carries an AtprotoRecordAnnotation (buzz.bookhive.book + generated codec).
  req F-3.2: Only fields marked AtprotoPublishAnnotation are eligible to publish; all others are private.
  req F-3.3: The codec provably never emits private fields (notes, ownership, personal tags).
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Create a book via autocomplete
  given: a space with the library plugin enabled
  when: the user searches "dune" and selects a result
  then: a Book is created with title, authors, coverUrl, genres, and hiveId populated

test T-2: Private fields never publish
  given: a Book with notes, owned, and personalTags set
  when: the codec encodes the book to a buzz.bookhive.book record
  then: the encoded record contains no notes, ownership, or personalTags data
```
